' @id(CMP-VIEWER-SHELL)
' @ref(USE-VIEW-DIAGRAMS)
' @desc(CMP-VIEWER-SHELL, "The egui shell of mdd-viewer as built by MddViewer::update: collapsible left/right SidePanels, a toolbar with no zoom buttons, and the center-fixed fisheye canvas stage that warps the rendered texture before painting.")
' Current-side component view derived from MddViewer::update in
' crates/mdd-viewer/src/lib.rs.
title mdd-viewer UI shell — ownership (current)

actor "Developer" as Dev <<added>>

component "MddViewer\n(eframe::App)\nupdate()" as Viewer
component "SidePanel left\n\"rail\" / sliver" as Left
component "SidePanel right\n\"context\" / sliver" as Right
component "svg_toolbar\n(PAGE selector + hint;\nno Reset/Zoom+/Zoom-)" as Toolbar
component "Fisheye canvas stage\nCanvasView::fisheye_mesh" as Fisheye
component "PanelLayout" as PL
component "CanvasView" as CV
component "eframe / egui 0.30\npainter.add(Shape::mesh)" as Egui

Dev --> Viewer : mdd view
Viewer --> Left : draw + collapse chevron / sliver
Viewer --> Right : draw + collapse chevron / sliver
Left --> PL : toggle_left()
Right --> PL : toggle_right()
Viewer --> Toolbar : draw (no zoom controls)
Viewer --> Fisheye : warp rendered texture per frame
Fisheye --> CV : focal=centre, strength, radius, warp()
Viewer --> Egui : textured Mesh, clipped to canvas rect
Egui --> Dev : centre-magnified diagram, collapsible panels

note bottom of Fisheye
  The fisheye is a display-time stage on top of the base
  zoom/pan placement; it does not change the render/font
  pipeline (CMP-VIEWER-RENDER-PIPELINE) — it only remaps
  where the already-rasterized texture is painted.
end note
@enduml
